      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right to be skeptical; the idea that wage hikes automatically save struggling businesses ignores the reality that a single shop might simply close due to elevated overhead, while another new competitor opens elsewhere with less resilience. While economic studies do point to a net positive in traditional retail, in your rural context, the margin for error is infinitesimal, and a single closure can critically reduce both local goods-generation and tax revenue. The real benefit likely comes from a more expanded, sustainable customer base rather than preventing specific small closures immediately. Ultimately, the \"good\" outcome only happens if the businesses you lose can be economically sustained in the long run by your community.",
